"I understand, your works are highly prized...so you would have a waiting list," her words were calm and respectful.  "I will wait until you let me know it is finished. Until then, it was nice to see you my son."  The low melodic tones in her voice seemed to almost show the truth in her statement.  At times, the motherly aspect in her surfaced...if not for very long.  <br>
Those icy orbs glanced to the others and she nodded in respect.  Then with a slight bend she picked up Eiliethyia and they both quickly dissappeared from the caverns. <p>~~<<<<<<{{{{@</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxgoddessaphrodite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xGoddess Aphrodite</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://graphicdesign.about.com/library/valentine/beat3.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(12/13/01 5:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.xenafan.com/gallery/if_the_shoe_fits/itsf254aphrodite27.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Looking about the room...</span><hr size=1> ::Aphrodite sat and faced Hera until she said her words and turned away from her. Aphrodite held her tongue from responding to Hera's sharp remarks.  By the Queen's body language, she was obviously still upset by the recent golden apple incident as well as the goddess of wisdom.  She slowly blinked her eyes and lean back in her chair, listening to the demands put upon her husband.  She would leave all of her battles outside of Hephaestus' home.::<br>
<br>
::She sees Hera's new child and blows her a kiss.  She could not take out the anger between her and hera on this prescious, little goddess.  She waves goodbye to her as she and her mother disappear.::: <p><3   Aphrodite ~ Goddess of Love and Beauty

</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=goddessathena>Goddess Athena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 84<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(12/13/01 7:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>  . . .</span><hr size=1> Athena was able to drop the golden bracelet into her sisters hand before they vanished.<br>
<br>
She stood up and turned looking at Hephaestus and Aphrodite. Her folded arms and other body language could signal the emotions towards Aphrodite at the moment.<br>
<br>
She then turned her eyes towards Hephaetus.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm going to need the spear soon, I have a feeling I'll be needing it.&quot;<br>
<br>
She looked at Dite.<br>
<br>
&quot;You can stay and watch of course, but I'm sure you have other men  . . . erm . .  things to attend to.&quot;<br>
<br>
Purses her lips and narrows her eyes at the &quot;Golden Appled Goddess.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxgoddessaphrodite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xGoddess Aphrodite</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://graphicdesign.about.com/library/valentine/beat3.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 167<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(12/15/01 4:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=204.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.xenafan.com/gallery/if_the_shoe_fits/itsf254aphrodite27.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:  . . .</span><hr size=1> ::Aphrodite narrows her eyes and tilted her head at the goddess of wisdom.  Again, she stays silent for she knows she is famous for her jaunts around the Olympian gods.  But to her it is perfectly justified.  She IS the goddess of love.  Why should just one person have the right to experience that was beyond her comprehension of a lustless virgin goddess.:::<br>
